claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: A table of licensed influenza vaccines listing trade names, presentations, age indications, hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content per virus per dose (µg HA/0.5 mL), administration route, and mercury content if present. Evidence: Flublok Quadrivalent (recombinant HA vaccine) is listed with 45 µg/0.5 mL HA per virus, whereas standard‐dose IIV4 vaccines are listed with 15 µg/0.5 mL per virus. does not support the claim: the table confirms Flublok contains three times the HA antigen content of standard‐dose flu vaccines but provides no information on immunogenicity or its comparison to standard‐dose vaccines.
